<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font size="5">Who is ZVI?</font><br /></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;">Zahroof Valves, Inc. (ZVI) is an innovative company, with its headquarters in Houston, Texas, that has developed and now markets the  revolutionary StraightFlo valve for use in reciprocating  gas compressors. The StraightFlo valve delivers a step change in valve performance,  serviceability and reliability. As a result of these proven and measured  improvements, ZVI is able to guarantee a 20% improvement in valve  efficiency and a 50% increase in service interval with an industry  leading 10 year warranty on the stainless steel valve housing.</div>

<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font size="5">Advanced Engineering</font><br /></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;">Zahroof Valves, Inc. uses state of the art engineering tools to design  its&nbsp;products and to provide support to its customers. Our valves are  designed using&nbsp;3D CAD, FEA, CFD and in-house proprietary programs that  include state of the art <br /> compressor simulation and valve dynamics software using NIST based real gas&nbsp;routines. <br /><span></span><br />Our  staff of engineers will optimize each valve for your&nbsp;particular  application so you can count on our guarantee for the best  in&nbsp;performance, reliability, and a substantial reduction in operational  cost.&nbsp;<br /> <br />In addition to custom-engineering the products we <br /> make, ZVI can provide engineering services for valve analysis, upgrades, and conversions.</div>

<div><div style="height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;"></div>
<hr class="styled-hr" style="width:100%;"></hr>
<div style="height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;"></div></div>


					
				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:46.309173925446%; padding:0 15px;">
					
						

<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font size="5">The Game Changer</font><br /></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;">Are you interested in the StraightFlo valve and seeing  first-hand how much better your compressors can perform with the SF valves in  place? If, so, <a title="" href="/contact-us.html">contact us</a>.<br /></div>

<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align:center;"><font size="5">Benefits of the StraightFlo valve</font><br /></h2>

<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><strong style="">Fuel savings of 5 &ndash; 15%:</strong> Measured field data on a  natural gas pipeline compressor running at 1000 rpm showed a 10%  reduction in operating power for the same work - $55,680 annual fuel  savings/compressor @ $3.0/MSCF natural gas.<br /><strong style="">More revenue:</strong> Increase flow through the same compressor by up to 15% at the same power with just a change in valves.<br /><strong style="">Longer</strong><strong style=""> life and higher reliability:&nbsp; </strong>StraightFlo valves have  no helical springs to break; seat and carrier never need to be machined; highest  natural frequency; safeguards against pulsation and other excitation  forces.&nbsp; The SF has the highest tolerance to liquids in the gas stream  and to foreign particles such as black powder.<br /><strong style="">The easiest valve to service, the lowest down-times</strong>:  No machining of seat or carrier, 5 &ndash; 10 minute turn-around time per  valve at your site; eliminates machining, special tools, skilled labor.<br /><strong style="">Lower inventory costs by &gt;80%:</strong>  Stock standard modules - not complete assembled valves unique to a  cylinder and application. Modules are interchangeable for different  stages and compressor brands.<br /><strong style="">Increase service interval:</strong> Proven valve design to further improve life of the valve.<br />Green operation: <strong>3</strong><strong style="">&nbsp;&ndash; 18% reduction in fuel consumption, emissions, and carbon footprint.  Minimize waste of material. Lowest noise level among valves.</strong><br />Industry Leading Warranty: <strong style="">Limited warranty of 10 years on valve housing.</strong><br />Optimized Valve For Your Application: ZVI uses an advanced compressor simulation and dynamic valve analysis program, using NIST real gas routines, to optimize valves for your application.</div>


					
				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:21.106769308008%; padding:0 15px;">
					
						

